<FTL>

<!-- Basically an extra vampiric weapon with various events and RadiKal-style spice. -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_COMBAT_SHIPVORE_RAM">
    <title>Shipvore Ram</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) Repeatedly ram the enemy for guaranteed damage, often free repairs, and sometimes other things.
		[See bonuses/combos in the Toggle Menu]

		Normal ramming: (cost {)
		2-3 damage, [style[color:ff3377]]25% bad outcomes![[/style]]

		Full Power: (cost 4{, [style[color:ff3377]]destroys the augment[[/style]]) 
		6-7 damage, [style[color:ff3377]]20% other bad outcomes![[/style]]
		
		Emergency Generator and Fuel Conserver can apply.

		Can be reinforced at empty beacons for some ~, to survive the next Full Power use. (Does not use up the beacon)</desc>
    <cost>70</cost>
	<!--<bp>4</bp>-->
    <rarity>3</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="LOCKED_DJMOD_COMBAT_SHIPVORE_RAM">
    <title>Shipvore Ram</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) Repeatedly ram the enemy for guaranteed damage, often free repairs, and sometimes other things.
		[See bonuses/combos in the Toggle Menu]

		Normal ramming: (cost {)
		2-3 damage, [style[color:ff3377]]25% bad outcomes![[/style]]

		Full Power: (cost 4{, [style[color:ff3377]]destroys the augment[[/style]]) 
		6-7 damage, [style[color:ff3377]]20% bad outcomes![[/style]]
		
		Emergency Generator and Fuel Conserver can apply.

		The ship was built around this locked version that survives Full Power use. Also gives 9% faster shield recharge and chance to ignore hull damage.</desc>
    <cost>200</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>


<augBlueprint name="RK_CREW_ARE_BOMBS_OFF">
    <title>Charged Belts (Off)</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) This augment is Off but can be toggled On anytime. When On:

	[This double-edged augment equips your crew with belts that [style[color:ff3377]]reduce their HP by 10% (beware of Vagabonds)[[/style]] and explode when they die, causing a fire and dealing damage to the room and ship they're in, with extra damage in systemless rooms. [style[color:ff3377]]Has friendly fire.[[/style]]
	Stacks upon already existing death effects.
	
	[style[color:ff3377]]WARNING: Can't be toggled Off.[[/style]] Can scrap itself into ~ or } at empty beacons.

	COMBO: Makes any crew a fire source for Plasma Teleporter.]</desc>
    <cost>50</cost>		
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="RK_CREW_ARE_BOMBS_ON">
    <title>Charged Belts</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) This double-edged augment equips your crew with belts that [style[color:ff3377]]reduce their HP by 10% (beware of Vagabonds)[[/style]] and explode when they die, causing a fire and dealing damage to the room and ship they're in, with extra damage in systemless rooms. [style[color:ff3377]]Has friendly fire.[[/style]]
	Stacks upon already existing death effects.
	
	[style[color:ff3377]]WARNING: Can't be toggled Off.[[/style]] Can scrap itself into ~ or } at empty beacons.

	COMBO: Makes any crew a fire source for Plasma Teleporter.</desc>
    <cost>50</cost>		
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- Can trigger immediately if below HP threshold when choosing to activate it in combat check. -->
<augBlueprint name="RK_COMBAT_AUTO_SYS_REPAIR">
    <title>A.E.R.A. Second Wind</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) 'Automated Emergency Repair Augment'.

		When you activate this Combat augment, if your ship is almost destroyed during the fight (9 Hull or less), a nanomachine burst is triggered, fully repairing your systems and 15 Hull points. [Activation uses 1 power, Emergency Generator can apply]
		[style[color:ff3377]]The effect also destroys the augment. No effect if your hull instantly reaches 0.[[/style]]
		
		You can also trigger this via the Toggle Menu anytime for 1{.
	</desc>
    <cost>60</cost>
    <rarity>3</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_LEAD_TITANS">
    <title>Lead Titans</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) Someone had the insane idea to weave motile fiber-lead into muscles. 
		
		Your 'big' crew (Crystals, Lanius, Rockmen, Saltmen) have: 2.5x resistance to everything, deal 2.5x damage to everything.
		[style[color:ff3377]]The weight makes them take 2 crew slots, create breaches while walking, and they can't repair.[[/style]]
		Your other crew get a flat +75% repair speed from smaller fibers.

		All your crew gain a flat +40% movement speed.
	
		[style[color:ff3377]]WARNING: Can't be toggled Off.[[/style]] Can scrap itself at empty beacons.</desc>
    <cost>70</cost>
    <rarity>4</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_BAM_DIVINE_ARMOR">
    <title>Thicker Hull</title>
    <desc>(RK Bam gear) RadiKals reverse engineered very rare armor from captured Theocracy inquisitors into this slightly more accessible and less perfect armor.
		
		[style[color:ff3377]]Reduces weapon charge speed by 5%.[[/style]]
		Impacts that deal 1 damage have a 40% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 1.
	</desc>
    <cost>120</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
	<value>0.4</value>			<!-- THIS IS THE CHANCE TO NEGATE 1-DAMAGE HITS via the Lua!!! -->
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_PERSISTENCE_SHIELD">
    <title>Persistence Shield</title>
	<desc>(RK Bam gear) A staple of high-end ships relying on Shields, made possible by stress tests on many Zoltan scouts who never came home.
		
		Adds a 4 hitpoints Super Shield. Stacks with other Super Shields, but not with itself.
		Also increases Shield charge speed by 25%.
		
		Activate from the Toggle Menu to instantly restore all your Supershield layers. [Uses 1 {]
		Cannot be activated again until you rebuild its capacitor at an empty beacon for 7~ .
	</desc>
    <cost>130</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
</FTL>

