<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_JUMP_DECOY">
    <title>Jump Decoy</title>
    <desc>When you escape a fight by performing an FTL jump, this sends a fake jump signature to a different destination. Your enemy has a 25% chance to transmit this misleading intel, delaying the rebel fleet for 1 turn.</desc>
    <cost>30</cost>
    <rarity>1</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

REWORKED JumpDecoy -->
<augBlueprint name="RK_COMBAT_HACK_FLEET">
    <title>Enigmashin</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) This combat augment tries to send deepfake intel to the rebels through an enemy's comms for credibility.
		
		"Success" delays the fleet by 1 ("Crit" by 2), failure does nothing, [style[color:ff3377]]"Crit-fail" accelerates the fleet by 1[[/style]].
		Free use takes 17 seconds. Limit your Hacking system and use droneparts for faster, better results. [style[color:ff3377]](Someone might notice)[[/style]]
		
		Chances: (Success / Crit / Crit-fail)
		0| + no hacking = 55% / 5% / 15%
		1| + hacking 1 = 60% / 10% / 10%
		2| + hacking 2 = 65% / 15% / 5% / +?
		3| + hacking 3 = 45% / 30% / 5% / +???</desc>
    <cost>35</cost>
    <rarity>3</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_DREAD_DECK">
    <title>Dread Deck</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) Doesn't directly do anything, but seasoned crew start praying and social distancing whenever this augment shows up.

		Enemies aboard your ship take 1.7x damage from everything.
		Your crew have 1.6x healing from most sources, 2x cloning speed, and lose no skills from cloning.
		[style[color:ff3377]]WARNING: All crew in the same room as any of your crew has 0.5x healing[[/style]] (does not stack) [style[color:ff3377]]and cannot be cloned![[/style]] [This debuff is purple smoke]</desc>
    <cost>120</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_SUPER_DEFENDERS">
    <title>Defense Kits</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) With all the risks they take, sometimes RadiKals need extra survivability. These kits include light motorized armor for all shapes and sizes, drugs, and other medical equipment.

		On your ship, your crew have 0.75x damage taken, 1.3x repair speed, 1.3x movement speed, and a 4 HP/second heal while idle (not even manning).</desc>
    <cost>90</cost>
    <rarity>4</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- Daft Punk H B F S reference -->
<augBlueprint name="RK_OWN_HARMONY_ON">
    <title>Punk Harmony</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) Some daft RadiKal Punks made their own Harmony. [style[color:ff3377]]Controls your Engis[[/style]] on your ship, giving them immunity to (further) mind control and +40% resistance to damage and stun. Powered levels in Hacking or Mind Control add 5/10/20/40/80/160% combat damage, repair speed, and movement speed.
	
	In short, makes them harder, better, faster, stronger, and automated.
	
	Can be toggled off anytime.

	At empty beacons, you can grow a Separatist for 25~, 1{ and 1|, but [style[color:ff3377]]the rebel fleet accelerates for 1 turn[[/style]]</desc>
    <cost>55</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="RK_OWN_HARMONY_OFF">
    <title>Punk Harmony (OFF)</title>
    <desc>(RK Punk gear) Some daft RadiKal Punks made their own Harmony. [style[color:ff3377]]Controls your Engis[[/style]] on your ship, giving them immunity to (further) mind control and +40% resistance to damage and stun. Powered levels in Hacking or Mind Control add 5/10/20/40/80/160% combat damage, repair speed, and movement speed.
	
	In short, makes them harder, better, faster, stronger, and automated.
	
	Can be toggled on anytime.

	At empty beacons, you can grow a Separatist for 25~, 1{ and 1|, but [style[color:ff3377]]the rebel fleet accelerates for 1 turn[[/style]]</desc>
    <cost>55</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
</FTL>

