<!-- Each level increases the fire resists.
The first one allows widespread own ship fire control (removal and creation) and survival, with heal. -->
<augBlueprint name="RK_SCORCH_SELF">
    <title>Scorched Earth (T1)</title>
    <desc>(RK Scorch gear) Your crew take 0.6x fire damage and get 3x extinguishing. While extinguishing, they also heal 2 HP/second, +2 per powered level in O2.
	
	Activate from the Toggles menu to set any system room [style[color:ff3377]]on your ship[[/style]] (or the whole ship) on fire to fight boarders.
	
	COMBO: Can activate Plasma Teleporter at no extra cost.
	
	Can be upgraded twice at empty beacons, increasing the fire resistance and gaining an effect.</desc>
    <cost>60</cost>
    <rarity>3</rarity>
	<!-- <value>1</value> This field is unneeded and can't fix system fire resistance. -->
    <!-- <stackable>false</stackable> -->
    <stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- Better res, potential infinity loop. -->
<augBlueprint name="RK_SCORCH_SELF_2">
    <title>Blazing Earth (T2)</title>
    <desc>(RK Scorch gear) [Tier 2 Scorched Earth] Your crew take 0.45x fire damage and get 3x extinguishing. While extinguishing, they also heal 2 HP/second, +2 per powered level in O2.
		In fire, they also produce O2 like 1 Orchid.
	
	Activate from the Toggles menu to set any system room [style[color:ff3377]]on your ship[[/style]] (or the whole ship) on fire to fight boarders.
	
	COMBO: Can activate Plasma Teleporter at no extra cost.
	
	Can be upgraded once at empty beacons, increasing the fire resistances and O2 production.</desc>
    <cost>90</cost>			
    <rarity>5</rarity>
	<!-- <value>1</value> This field is unneeded and can't fix system fire resistance. -->
    <!-- <stackable>false</stackable> -->
    <stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- Better res, facilitate infinity loop. -->
<augBlueprint name="RK_SCORCH_SELF_3">
    <!-- <title>Molten Earth</title> -->
	<title>Erupting Earth (T3)</title>
    <desc>(RK Scorch gear) [Tier 3 Scorched Earth] Your crew take 0.3x fire damage and get 3x extinguishing. While extinguishing, they also heal 2 HP/second, +2 per powered level in O2.
		In fire, they also produce O2 like 3 Orchids.
	
	Activate from the Toggles menu to set any system room [style[color:ff3377]]on your ship[[/style]] (or the whole ship) on fire to fight boarders.
	
	COMBO: Can activate Plasma Teleporter at no extra cost.</desc>
    <cost>120</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
	<!-- <value>1</value> This field is unneeded and can't fix system fire resistance. -->
    <!-- <stackable>false</stackable> -->
    <stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>


<augBlueprint name="RK_COMBAT_SCORCH_ENEMY">
	<title>Plasma Teleporter</title>
	<desc>(RK Scorch gear) This combat augment can set the enemy ship on fire at start of combat, outright winning some fights.

		Needs a fire source: 1} (weak effect),
		or: Uptor/Goul/Lost Sun/Shell/Zoltan ([style[color:ff3377]]they die[[/style]], can be cloned, strong effect).
		Using a Ghost has an extra effect.
		[Uses 1{, [style[color:ff3377]]ignites your O2 system[[/style]].]

	COMBO: Charged Belts / Martyr Vests make all crew fire sources.
	COMBO: any Scorched Earth removes the need for a fire source.</desc>
	<cost>75</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_ENEMIES_CAN_BURN">
	<title>Flammabilizer-Immune</title>
	<desc>(RK Scorch gear) Passively removes the fire immunity of enemies, and limits their fire resistance to 0%. Enemies who invert fire damage stop doing that. Vulnerable enemies (like Orchids) are unaffected.
	Works on both ships.

	Can be toggled anytime to make non-fireproof enemies take more fire damage instead.

	Both toggle modes make enemies move 20% slower in fire (up to 80% with 3 power in O2) [Does not stack].</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="RK_ENEMIES_BURN_MORE">
	<title>Flammabilizer-Damage</title>
	<desc>(RK Scorch gear) Passively makes enemies who can burn take 60% more fire damage, scaling up to 300% with 4+ power in your Life Support (O2) system.
	Works on both ships.
	
	Can be toggled anytime to make fireproof, fire-resistant and fire-healing enemies vulnerable to fire instead.

	Both toggle modes make enemies move 20% slower in fire (up to 80% with 3 power in O2) [Does not stack].</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_COMBAT_OXYGENIZER">
	<title>Oxygenizer</title>
	<desc>(RK Scorch gear) This little Combat Augment can shoot out giant gravity-inducing canisters of ultracompressed O2 to fill the void of space when a fight starts. Some nickname it "Canned Air". Shenanigans ensue.
	
	Puts both ships in an atmosphere, making breaches and open vents fill oxygen instead of depleting it. [Uses 2}]</desc>
	<cost>20</cost>
	<rarity>4</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_SCORCH_PREIGNITER">
	<title>Scorch Pre-Igniter</title>
	<desc>(RK Scorch gear) Your weapons are made immediately available after an FTL jump but [style[color:ff3377]]they light a fire in the Weapons room every time they shoot a projectile or beam[[/style]].
		
		This variant of the famous Weapon Pre-igniters is flawed and does not count as one for events or Aether tech requirements, but at least it's more accessible.
		
		COMBO: Increases "Weapons On Fire" augment's max extra bonus to 20%</desc>
	<cost>115</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="RK_WEAPONS_ON_FIRE">
	<title>Weapons On Fire</title>
	<desc>(RK Scorch gear) The fire rate of your Weapons and Artilleries is improved by 25%.
		Gain an extra 1% fire rate every time they shoot a projectile or beam (up to 10% - does not stack with multiple Weapons On Fire), but at the same time there's a [style[color:ff3377]]15% chance to light a fire in your Weapon Control and any Artillery rooms[[/style]].
		The extra bonus is reset on jump.

		COMBO: Scorch Preigniter increases the maximum extra bonus to 20%</desc>
	<cost>135</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<value>0.15</value>		<!-- Chance of fire. intended: 0.15 -->
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="RK_WEAPONS_ON_FIRE_TEMP">
	<title>Weapons On Fire</title>
	<desc>YOU SHOULD NEVER SEE THIS 1% weapon fire rate.</desc>
	<cost>0</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
</FTL>

